						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar set up near the image of Hanumān.</p>						

						<p>Mallikārjuna, 1453 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 137[5], Śrīmukha, Bhādrapada śu. 15, Sunday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1453 A.D., August 19.</hi></p>						

						<p>It seems to register a gift of ten <hi rend="italic">māḍas</hi> to a Brāhman for the merit of Siṅgi-sāni. The record is much damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
